      <data key="d8">INFECTION RISK</data>
      <data key="d9">REDUCES</data>
      <data key="d10">Higher air exchange rates decrease the likelihood of airborne pathogen accumulation, thereby reducing infection risk. | Higher ACH levels outperform lower levels in reducing infection risk by increasing ventilation efficiency.</data>
